    # Nonprofits & Activism
    {"Category": "Nonprofits & Activism", "Description": "The Trevor Project is the leading suicide prevention and crisis intervention organization for LGBTQ+ young people. reach out to us at 866-488-7386, text 678-678, or visit TheTrevorProject.org/Help"},
    {"Category": "Nonprofits & Activism", "Description": "Human Rights Watch is one of the world’s leading independent organizations dedicated to defending and protecting human rights. By focusing international attention where human rights are violated, we give voice to the oppressed and hold oppressors accountable for their crimes. Our rigorous, objective investigations and strategic, targeted advocacy build intense pressure for action and raise the cost of human rights abuse."},
    {"Category": "Nonprofits & Activism", "Description": "Greenpeace exists because this fragile earth deserves a voice. It needs solutions. It needs change. It needs action!"},
    {"Category": "Nonprofits & Activism", "Description": "You are watching Animal Rights Television®. People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals (PETA) is the largest animal rights organization in the world, and PETA entities have more than 9 million members and supporters globally."},
    {"Category": "Nonprofits & Activism", "Description": "The Nature Conservancy is a global conservation organization dedicated to conserving the lands and waters on which all life depends. Guided by science, we create innovative, on-the-ground solutions to our world's toughest challenges so that nature and people can thrive together. We are tackling climate change, conserving lands, waters and oceans at an unprecedented scale, providing food and water sustainably and helping make cities more sustainable. Working in 81 countries and territories, we use a collaborative approach that engages local communities, governments, the private sector, and other partners."},
    {"Category": "Nonprofits & Activism", "Description": "Doctors Without Borders/Médecins Sans Frontières (MSF) offers medical humanitarian assistance to people based solely on need, irrespective of race, religion, gender, or political affiliation. Our teams of doctors, nurses, logisticians, and other frontline workers are often among the first on the scene when peoples’ lives are upended by conflict, disease outbreaks, or natural or human-made disasters. We believe that the principles of impartiality and neutrality are not synonymous with silence. When the world turns its back on crises, we are duty-bound to raise our voices and speak out on behalf of our patients. Our decision to do so is always guided by our mission to do no harm, preserve respect and dignity, and protect life and health."},
    {"Category": "Nonprofits & Activism", "Description": "The American Cancer Society is the leading cancer-fighting organization with a vision to end cancer as we know it, for everyone. We are the only organization improving the lives of people with cancer and their families through advocacy, research, and patient support, to ensure that everyone has an opportunity to prevent, detect, treat, and survive cancer. We are available day or night, at 1-800-227-2345 or by visiting cancer.org."},
    {"Category": "Nonprofits & Activism", "Description": "Videos created by, for, and/or about the American Red Cross. The American Red Cross is a charitable organization, not a government agency. It depends on volunteers and the generosity of people like you to perform our mission."},
    {"Category": "Nonprofits & Activism", "Description": "The Sierra Club is America's largest and most influential grassroots environmental organization with more than 3 million members and supporters nationwide. In addition to creating opportunities for people of all ages, levels and locations to have meaningful outdoor experiences, the Sierra Club works to safeguard the health of our communities, protect wildlife, and preserve our remaining wild places through grassroots activism, public education, lobbying and litigation. For more information, visit http://www.sierraclub.org."},
    {"Category": "Nonprofits & Activism", "Description": "Here, we share exciting, entertaining, and informative content across a variety of topics. Whether you’re here for [list a few topics your videos cover, e.g., tech reviews, vlogs, tutorials, Facts, stories, Autos & Vehicles Comedy Education Entertainment Film & Animation Gaming Howto & Style Music News & Politics Nonprofits & Activism People & Blogs Pets & Animal Science & Technology Sports Travel & Events or challenges], we’ve got something for everyone."},

